Chapter 3 Exercises

Exercise 1

 library(tidyverse)
nm_college19 <- get_acs(
  geography = "county",
  variables = "DP02_0068P",
  state = "NM",
  survey = "acs5",
  year = 2019
)
nm_college19
nm_hi_pct <- nm_college19 %>%
  arrange(desc(estimate)) %>%
  filter(estimate>50)

nm_hi_pct

The NM county with the highest percentage of residents over 25 with a Bachelor’s degree is Los Alamos County, New Mexico, with an estimated 67.4%.

nm_lo_pct <- nm_college19 %>%
  arrange(estimate) %>%
  slice_min(n = 1, estimate)
nm_lo_pct

The NM county with the highest percentage of residents over 25 with a Bachelor’s degree is Guadalupe County, New Mexico, with an estimated 7.6%.

nm_med_pct <- nm_college19 %>%
  separate(
    NAME,
    into = c("county","state"),
    sep = ", "
  )%>%
  group_by(state)%>%
  summarize(median_pct = median (estimate))

nm_med_pct

The average percentage of county residents over 25 in NM with a Bachelor’s degree is 18.5%.

Chapter 4 Exercises

Exercise 1

library(tidyverse)
nm_house_val <-get_acs(
    geography = "county",
    state = "NM",
    variables = c(value = "B25077_001"),
    year = 2019
    ) %>%
  separate(NAME, into = c("county", "state"), sep = ", ")%>%
  mutate(county = str_remove(county, " County"))
nm_house_val
ggplot(nm_house_val, aes(x = estimate, y = reorder(county, estimate))) + 
  geom_errorbarh(aes(xmin = estimate - moe, xmax = estimate + moe)) + 
  geom_point(size = 3, color = "darkred") + 
  theme_gray(base_size = 10) + 
  labs(title = "Median home value", 
       subtitle = "Counties in New Mexico", 
       x = "2015-2019 ACS estimate", 
       y = "") + 
  scale_x_continuous(labels = scales::dollar)

Exercise 2

nm_pop <- get_estimates(
  geography = "state",
  state = "NM",
  product = "characteristics",
  breakdown = c("SEX", "AGEGROUP"),
  breakdown_labels = TRUE,
  year = 2019
) 
nm_filtered <- filter(nm_pop, str_detect(AGEGROUP, "^Age"), 
                  SEX != "Both sexes") %>%
  mutate(value = ifelse(SEX == "Male", -value, value))
nm_filtered
nm_pyramid <- ggplot(nm_filtered, 
                       aes(x = value, 
                           y = AGEGROUP, 
                           fill = SEX)) + 
  geom_col(width = 0.95, alpha = 1.00) + 
  theme_minimal(base_family = "Verdana", 
                base_size = 12) + 
  scale_x_continuous(labels = function(x) paste0(abs(x / 1000), "k")) + 
  scale_y_discrete(labels = function(y) str_remove_all(y, "Age\\s|\\syears")) + 
  scale_fill_manual(values = c("#BA0C2F", "#008080")) + 
  labs(x = "", 
       y = "2019 Census Bureau population estimate", 
       title = "Population structure in New Mexico", 
       fill = "", 
       caption = "Data source: US Census Bureau population estimates & tidycensus R package")
nm_pyramid
